data.content:
Memory Management	Operating System
core function,system responsibility
The Operating System is responsible for managing memory through allocation, recovery, and protection.

Main Memory	Memory Management
dynamic allocation,physical resource management
Memory Management controls how main memory is allocated and used by processes.

Memory Management	Program and Data
memory access,storage requirement
Memory Management ensures that programs and data are stored and accessed efficiently in main memory.

Memory Management	Virtual Storage Technology
logical expansion,memory simulation
Virtual Storage Technology allows memory management to expand system memory logically beyond physical limits.

Multi-Programming	Operating System
concurrent execution,resource management
The Operating System enables multi-programming by managing memory allocation between multiple processes.

Logical Address	Memory Management
address translation,mapping
Memory Management translates logical addresses used by programs into physical addresses for memory access.

Memory Management	Physical Address
address resolution,memory placement
Memory Management maps logical addresses to physical addresses in main memory.

Memory Management	Memory Space Allocation
memory distribution,process execution
Memory Management assigns memory space to active processes during runtime.

Memory Management	Memory Space Recovery
process termination,resource reclaim
Memory Management recovers memory space after a process ends to free it for other uses.

Memory Management	Memory Sharing
coordination,multi-process access
Memory Management enables controlled access to shared memory regions by multiple processes.

Memory Management	Storage Protection
isolation,security
Memory Management ensures that processes are isolated and cannot interfere with each other’s memory space.

最佳置换算法	页面置换算法
algorithm variant,theoretical benchmark
The Optimal (OPT) page replacement algorithm is a variant of the page replacement algorithm designed as a theoretical benchmark for minimum page fault rate.

先进先出置换算法	页面置换算法
algorithm variant,implementation method
The First-In-First-Out (FIFO) algorithm is a common implementation method of the page replacement algorithm.

最佳置换算法	缺页率
optimization goal,performance metric
The optimal page replacement algorithm is designed to achieve the lowest possible page fault rate.

data.src_id: 最近最久未使用置换算法
data.content:
最近最久未使用置换算法	页面置换算法
algorithm variant,performance-driven
The Least Recently Used (LRU) algorithm is a performance-optimized variant of the page replacement algorithm.

Belady异常	先进先出置换算法
algorithm limitation,performance anomaly
Belady’s anomaly is a performance limitation specific to the FIFO page replacement algorithm.

data.src_id: 最近最久未使用置换算法
data.content:
最近最久未使用置换算法	硬件支持
implementation requirement,performance cost
The LRU algorithm requires hardware support like registers and stacks, increasing its implementation cost.

时钟置换算法	页面置换算法
algorithm variant,practical approximation
The Clock algorithm is a practical approximation of the LRU algorithm used to reduce hardware complexity.

先进先出置换算法	物理块
impact on performance,resource constraint
The number of physical blocks affects the performance of the FIFO algorithm, including the occurrence of Belady’s anomaly.

改进型时钟置换算法	时钟置换算法
algorithm enhancement,enhanced version
The Enhanced Clock algorithm is an improved version of the basic Clock algorithm that incorporates both access and modify bits for better decisions.

访问位	页面置换算法
data support,usage tracking
The access bit is used in various page replacement algorithms to track whether a page has been recently accessed.

修改位	改进型时钟置换算法
data field,replacement decision
The modify bit is used in the Enhanced Clock algorithm to evaluate replacement cost during page eviction.

1类页面	改进型时钟置换算法
best candidate,eviction priority
The Enhanced Clock algorithm prioritizes 1-class pages for eviction because they are least likely to be needed again and have not been modified.

2类页面	改进型时钟置换算法
eviction priority,second best
The Enhanced Clock algorithm considers 2-class pages as the next best eviction candidates after 1-class pages.

3类页面	改进型时钟置换算法
eviction priority,keep consideration
The Enhanced Clock algorithm avoids evicting 3-class pages during a round and may retain them for another cycle.

4类页面	改进型时钟置换算法
avoid eviction,eviction priority
The Enhanced Clock algorithm avoids evicting 4-class pages, as they are recently accessed and modified, indicating high potential for reuse.

Memory-Mapped Files	System Call
abstraction,operating system interface
Memory-Mapped Files is implemented via a system call provided by the operating system.

Disk File	Memory-Mapped Files
data access,file mapping
Memory-Mapped Files establish a mapping between a disk file and a process’s virtual address space for efficient data access.

Memory-Mapped Files	Process Virtual Address Space
memory mapping,virtual addressing
Memory-Mapped Files map a disk file into a process’s virtual address space.

Memory-Mapped Files	Operating System
file I/O handling,resource management
The operating system manages the mapping, loading, and persistence of memory-mapped files.

Memory-Mapped Files	Page
on-demand loading,page-wise loading
Only when a page is accessed is it loaded from disk into memory, enabling lazy loading.

File Content	Memory-Mapped Files
memory-like operations,transparent access
File content is accessed as if it were memory, with read/write operations appearing to be direct memory access.

Memory-Mapped Files	Multiple Processes
inter-process communication,shared access
Multiple processes can share the same memory-mapped file, enabling data sharing and coordination.

Memory-Mapped Files	Shared Memory
data sharing,memory efficiency
Memory-Mapped Files facilitate shared memory across processes, allowing them to access and modify the same data.

Memory-Mapped Files	Performance Optimization
efficiency,reduced I/O overhead
Memory-Mapped Files improve performance by reducing the need for explicit read/write system calls and enabling lazy loading.

Memory-Mapped Files	Virtual Memory
address space management,similar abstraction
Memory-Mapped Files share conceptual similarities with virtual memory by using address space abstraction and paging.

空闲分区链	首次适应算法
allocation strategy,search method
First Fit algorithm searches the free partition chain in order of ascending address to find the first suitable partition.

动态分区分配	外部碎片
allocation inefficiency,memory fragmentation
Dynamic partition allocation leads to the formation of external fragmentation over time due to frequent memory allocation and deallocation.

伙伴系统	快速适应算法
classification,memory allocation method
Fast Fit and the buddy system are both allocation methods that organize free partitions by size, though Fast Fit uses multiple chains while the buddy system enforces power-of-two sizes.

哈希算法	空闲分区链表
data structure,fast lookup
Hash algorithm uses a hash table based on partition size to quickly locate the head of a corresponding free partition chain.

邻近适应算法	首次适应算法
algorithm variant,search continuation
Next Fit is a variant of First Fit that continues the search from the last position, improving search efficiency.

最佳适应算法	空闲分区链
allocation strategy,size-based selection
Best Fit algorithm selects the smallest partition that fits the request from the free partition chain sorted by size.

内存利用率	外部碎片
performance impact,resource efficiency
External fragmentation negatively affects memory utilization by creating small, unusable memory blocks.

动态分区分配	紧凑技术
fragmentation resolution,memory management
Compact technology is used to resolve external fragmentation in dynamic partition allocation by rearranging memory contents.

最坏适应算法	空闲分区链
allocation strategy,largest fit
Worst Fit algorithm selects the largest available partition from the free partition chain ordered by size.

快速适应算法	空闲分区链
allocation strategy,size classification
Fast Fit algorithm organizes free partitions by common size classes, each with its own free partition chain for faster allocation.

动态分区分配	空闲分区链
allocation tracking,data structure
The free partition chain is a key data structure used in dynamic partition allocation for tracking available memory blocks.

段号	逻辑地址

逻辑地址包含段号，用于定位进程的逻辑段。

分页存储管理	段页式存储管理
combined method,integration
段页式存储管理结合了分页存储管理的物理内存分配方式。

每个段对应一张页表，段表中记录页表的起始地址。

段页式存储管理结合了分段存储管理的逻辑段划分方式。

address component,paging
逻辑地址包含页号，用于定位段中的页面。

段页式存储管理中，进程的地址空间首先划分为多个逻辑段。

地址变换过程首先通过段表查找页表的起始地址。

每个逻辑段进一步被划分为若干固定大小的页面。

逻辑地址	页内偏移量
address component,offset
逻辑地址包含页内偏移量，用于定位页面内的具体位置。

地址变换	页表
address translation,lookup
地址变换过程通过页表查找物理块号。

段页式存储管理	物理块
memory allocation,physical unit
内存被划分为与页面大小相同的物理块，分配以物理块为单位。

地址变换	物理地址
final address,result
地址变换最终生成物理地址，用于内存访问。

二维地址空间	段页式存储管理
address model,structural
段页式存储管理支持二维地址空间，由段和页构成。

装入模块	链接

Linking produces a complete load module ready for execution.

用户源程序	编译
code processing,source transformation
The user source program is processed by the compilation method to generate object code (target modules).

创建进程	程序的链接与装入
process initiation,program preparation
Creating a process requires the steps of linking and loading to prepare a user program for execution in memory.

可重定位装入	绝对装入
memory loading method comparison
Absolute loading and relocatable loading are different approaches to memory placement, with the former used in single-program environments and the latter allowing dynamic displacement.

装入	装入模块
execution preparation,memory loading
The load module is moved into memory using the loading method for execution.

动态运行时装入	重定位
dynamic relocation support,runtime address conversion
Dynamic runtime loading uses relocation during execution, enabled by the use of a relocation register.

实际内存地址	逻辑地址
address translation,memory mapping
Logical addresses are converted to actual memory addresses during loading or execution to enable correct program execution.

目标模块	编译
intermediate file creation,output generation
Compilation produces multiple target modules as output from the source code.

装入时动态链接	静态链接
flexibility,linking time comparison
Static linking occurs before execution, while loading-time dynamic linking allows more flexibility and shared code usage.

可重定位装入	重定位
address adjustment,loading phase
In relocatable loading, relocation is performed during the loading phase to convert logical addresses into physical addresses.

动态运行时装入	重定位寄存器
dynamic relocation,hardware support
Dynamic runtime loading requires a relocation register to store the base address of the loaded module.

目标模块	链接
input assembly,module integration
Linking combines target modules and their required library functions into a single load module.

装入时动态链接	运行时动态链接
linking timing,memory efficiency
Loading-time dynamic linking links modules during load, while runtime dynamic linking links only when needed, saving memory space.

不连续的存储区	动态运行时装入
dynamic allocation,memory flexibility
Dynamic runtime loading supports placing programs in non-contiguous memory regions.

动态运行时装入	程序段的共享
code sharing,memory efficiency
Dynamic runtime loading enables sharing of program segments among multiple processes, reducing memory usage.

Free Page List	Page Buffering Algorithm
memory management,page reuse
The Page Buffering Algorithm utilizes the Free Page List to hold unmodified pages temporarily without immediate disk I/O, improving efficiency.

Kswapd	Page Frame Recycling

Kswapd is the system process that performs page frame recycling when memory pressure is detected.

请求分页存储管理	页表机制

Page table mechanisms are essential for tracking logical-to-physical page mappings in request paging.

段表机制	请求分段存储管理
data structure support,memory mapping
Segment tables are used to manage the mapping of logical segments to physical memory.

局部性原理	虚拟内存

Virtual memory relies on the principle of locality to efficiently manage memory usage.

Kswapd	Memory Usage Threshold

Kswapd checks memory usage and activates page frame recycling when free pages fall below the Memory Usage Threshold.

The Page Buffering Algorithm uses the Modified Page List to delay writing modified pages to disk until a sufficient number are collected, reducing I/O overhead.

Page Frame Recycling	User-Process Page Frames

Page Frame Recycling primarily targets user-process page frames, as they are safe to reclaim.

多次性	虚拟存储器

Virtual storage supports loading programs in multiple stages rather than all at once.

中断机构	请求分页存储管理

The interrupt mechanism triggers when a required page is not in memory during execution in request paging.

data.content:
内存-外存两级存储器结构	虚拟内存
architecture foundation,system design
Virtual memory is implemented using a two-level storage system of main memory and secondary storage.

Kernel-Used Page Frames	Page Frame Recycling
memory protection,non-reclaimable
Kernel-used page frames are generally not eligible for recycling to ensure system stability.

对换性	虚拟存储器
feature,memory swapping
Virtual storage allows temporary removal of inactive data from memory to secondary storage.

物理地址	逻辑地址
address mapping,translation
Logical addresses are translated into physical addresses via the address transformation mechanism.

内存	外存
secondary storage,storage hierarchy
Memory and external storage form the hierarchical storage system used in virtual memory.

中断机构	请求分段存储管理
error handling,operation trigger
The interrupt mechanism signals the OS when a required segment is not present in memory.

虚拟内存	请求分页存储管理
implementation method,memory management
Virtual memory is implemented using request paging, where pages are loaded on demand.

虚拟存储器	虚拟性
feature,logical memory expansion
Virtual storage creates the illusion of a larger memory space than physically available.

逻辑地址	页表机制
memory mapping,translation
The page table mechanism maps logical addresses to physical addresses in page-based systems.

虚拟内存	请求分段存储管理
implementation method,memory management
Virtual memory can be implemented using request segmentation, where segments are loaded as needed.

外存	对换区
storage location,swap space
The swap area is a region on secondary storage used for storing inactive memory pages.

段表机制	逻辑地址
memory mapping,translation
The segment table mechanism maps logical segment addresses to physical memory.

虚拟内存	请求段页式存储管理
implementation method,memory management
Virtual memory uses a hybrid approach combining segmentation and paging, loading segments and pages on demand.

Single Continuous Allocation	System Area
memory partitioning
In single continuous allocation, the memory is partitioned into a system area for operating system use and a user area for user programs.

Single Continuous Allocation	User Area
memory partitioning
The user area is dedicated to a single user program, with the entire space being allocated to it.

Single Continuous Allocation	User Program
containment,resource allocation
The user program is the sole occupant of the user area, requiring exclusive and contiguous memory allocation.

Internal Fragmentation	Single Continuous Allocation
memory inefficiency,side effect
Internal fragmentation occurs because the allocated memory block may be larger than the actual program size, resulting in unutilized space.

Memory Utilization	Single Continuous Allocation
drawback,performance limitation
Memory utilization is extremely low because only one program runs at a time, leaving the majority of memory unused.

External Fragmentation	Single Continuous Allocation
absence of fragmentation
This method avoids external fragmentation because only one program is loaded and memory is managed in one contiguous block.

Memory Protection	Single Continuous Allocation
lack of requirement
Memory protection is not needed because only one user program operates in the user area, eliminating risk of interference.

Basic Page Storage Management	Page Frame
allocation,memory division
Basic page storage management divides physical memory into page frames for the allocation of process pages.

Page	Page Size
boundary definition,size specification
The size of a page is fixed and must be a power of 2, defining its boundaries within the logical address space.

Page Table	Page Table Entry
composition,mapping data,structure,table structure
Each page table contains one page table entry per page, which maps a logical page number to a physical block number.<SEP>The Page Table consists of multiple Page Table Entries, each representing a virtual page.

Page Frame	Physical Block

The terms page frame and physical block are interchangeable terms referring to the same physical memory unit.

Logical Address Space	Page
logical division,page assignment
The logical address space is divided into pages of equal size, each assigned a page number.

Physical Address	Physical Block Number

A physical address is created by combining the physical block number and the page offset.<SEP>The Physical Address is formed by combining the Physical Block Number with the page offset.

Page Number	Page Table

The page table uses page numbers as keys to locate corresponding physical block numbers.

Basic Page Storage Management	Page
logical organization,memory division
Basic page storage management logically divides a process's address space into pages for memory management.

Logical Address	Page Number
address decomposition,structure
A logical address is decomposed into a page number and a page offset during address translation.

Page Table	Page Table Register
register configuration,storage reference
The page table register holds the starting address and length of the page table in memory.

Page Number	Page Table Length
access control,boundary check
The page table length is used to verify if a page number is within bounds, preventing memory access violations.

Fast Table	Translation Lookaside Buffer
alternative name,synonymy
The TLB is also referred to as the fast table due to its high-speed lookup capability.

Logical Address	Page Offset
address decomposition,structure
A logical address is split into a page number and a page offset to locate the required data within the page.

Basic Address Transformation Mechanism	Page Table
address resolution,hardware implementation
The basic address transformation mechanism uses the page table to map logical addresses to physical addresses.

Outer Page Table	Two-Level Page Table
hierarchical structure,memory optimization
The two-level page table uses an outer page table to store the base addresses of second-level page tables, reducing memory usage.

Basic Address Transformation Mechanism	Page Table Register
hardware support,register access
The basic address transformation mechanism relies on the page table register to locate the page table in memory.

Page Table	Translation Lookaside Buffer
cache function,performance enhancement,synchronization,update
The TLB caches frequently accessed page table entries to accelerate address translation, reducing memory access overhead.<SEP>When a page table entry is accessed, it may be copied into the Translation Lookaside Buffer to enhance speed.

Outer Page Table	Page Directory

The terms outer page table and page directory are used interchangeably to refer to the top-level table in a two-level page table system.

Second-Level Page Number	Two-Level Page Table

The second-level page number is used to index into the second-level page table after accessing the outer page table.

Page Table	Slow Table

The main memory page table is used as the slow table when the TLB does not contain a required mapping.

Page Directory Register	Two-Level Page Table

The page directory register stores the base address of the outer page table for initializing the two-level page table lookup.

Multi-Level Page Table	Two-Level Page Table
extension,scalability
The multi-level page table is an extension of the two-level approach, designed to support larger address spaces.

Page Directory Base Address Register	Page Directory Register

The page directory register and the page directory base address register are synonymous terms referring to the same hardware register that holds the base address of the page directory.

Page Fault Rate	Resident Set Size

A smaller resident set size increases the likelihood of page faults, leading to higher page fault rates.

Global Replacement	Variable Allocation

Variable allocation with global replacement enables efficient memory reallocation across processes based on current needs.

Fixed Allocation	Local Replacement

Fixed allocation with local replacement ensures stable memory assignment and replacement within the same process.

Average Allocation Algorithm	Physical Page Frame

The average allocation algorithm ensures fair distribution of physical page frames among processes.

Multiprogramming Degree	Resident Set Size

Smaller resident sets allow more processes to be loaded into memory, increasing multiprogramming degree.

Page Fault Rate	Preloading Page Strategy

Preloading pages reduces future page faults by anticipating access patterns.

Disk I/O Speed	Swap Area

The swap area provides faster disk I/O for page swapping compared to the file area.

Local Replacement	Variable Allocation

Variable allocation with local replacement dynamically adjusts memory based on process behavior while preventing interference between processes.

Demand Page Strategy	Page Fault

Physical Page Frame	Proportional Allocation Algorithm

Demand Paging	Virtual Memory
core technique,memory extension
Demand paging is a fundamental component of virtual memory systems, enabling efficient memory usage.

Page Frame Allocation	Resident Set Size

Fixed Allocation	Variable Allocation

Fixed and variable allocation are mutually exclusive strategies for assigning physical page frames to processes.

Global Replacement	Local Replacement

Global and local replacement are mutually exclusive page replacement strategies.

File Area	UNIX Method

The UNIX method loads unexecuted pages from the file area at the start of process execution.

Request-Paging System	Swap Area
page replacement,storage dependency
The request-paging system uses the swap area for storing pages that have been swapped out from physical memory.

File Area	Request-Paging System

The request-paging system uses the file area to store program images and files not currently in memory.

response,trigger
The Page Fault Interrupt activates the Page Fault Handler to manage the process of loading the missing page.

Basic Paging System	Request Paging System
enhancement,foundation
The Request Paging System is built upon the Basic Paging System to support virtual memory.

Page Table Entry	Status Bit P
attribute,metadata
The Status Bit P is one of the four fields within a Page Table Entry that tracks in-memory status.

enabling technology,functional integration
The Request Paging System supports the functionality of virtual memory by providing demand paging and page replacement.

Page Frame	Page Replacement Algorithm
management,selection
The Page Replacement Algorithm selects which Page Frame to free when no free frames are available.

attribute,metadata

caching,performance optimization
